Defendant Darrell Gauthier in court with attorney Stephen A Sargent.  Defendant Darrell Gauthier in custody.  Jesica A Ballenger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by the state, defense, and defendant. 

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 52 MONTHS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 37 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 22 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 30 MONTHS.  The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS eligible the Substance Abuse Program.

This Court orders this sentence STAYED and places the defendant on probation for 3 YEARS with the following conditions:

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Corrections with release privileges to day reporting center for treatment.  NO ELECTRONIC MONITORING ALLOWED.
*Obtain Mental health assessment- complete follow-up treatment;
*Take any and all prescription medication only in the manner/dosage as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment- complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety, no drugs or alcohol- random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No illegal drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers/houses);
*Cooperate with all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or  full time school with part time work;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample if not previously submitted- pay surcharge;  

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $800.00 payable to Gary S.- to be paid first. The Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $600.00 plus all mandatory costs, penalties, surcharges, including $50.00 ignition interlock surcharge and $17.50 to West Allis Police Department (reimbursement for lab testing).  Court related costs and restitution to be paid by the end of probation period.  Any amount remaining to convert to civil judgment.   Court ordered AODA assessment and Driver's Safety Plan.  Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for a period of 24 months.  Court ordered defendant restricted to operation of vehicles equipped with an ignition interlock device for 24 months. If revoked, the Court ordered that all financial obligations and restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.
